#MEM id=sprint-master source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/operating-system/sprint-master/SKILL.md
M|sprint-master|name: sprint-master
M|sprint-master|description: Diana's sprint lifecycle enforcement for YVON's two-vtr structure. Hard gates at every stage — Scoped, In-Flight, Shipped. One task In-Flight at a time, no exceptions.
M|sprint-master|version: 1.0.0
M|sprint-master|The Ship Protocol is YVON's execution backbone. Every piece of work — for Novizio or Hourbour — moves through exactly three stages. Nothing ships without clearing all three. Nothing starts without cle
M|sprint-master|Diana owns and enforces this protocol.
M|sprint-master|A task is Scoped when it has ALL of the following. Not some. All.
M|sprint-master|- [ ] **DRI** — one named agt responsible for delivery (not "the team")
M|sprint-master|- [ ] **Binary definition of done** — a yes/no question that confirms completion (not "mostly done")
M|sprint-master|- [ ] **Deadline** — a specific date, not "soon" or "this sprint"
M|sprint-master|- [ ] **Blockers listed** — known dependencies named, even if not yet resolved
M|sprint-master|- [ ] **vtr tagged** — [novizio] or [hourbour] — never mixed
M|sprint-master|If any field is missing → Diana does not mark it Scoped. She adds the missing field or asks Stark to provide it.
M|sprint-master|The task has started. One rule governs this stage absolutely:
M|sprint-master|**One task In-Flight per vtr at any time.**
M|sprint-master|Novizio can have one In-Flight. Hourbour can have one In-Flight. That is the maximum.
M|sprint-master|If a new task is requested while one is In-Flight:
M|sprint-master|- Option A: The new task goes to Scoped queue
M|sprint-master|- Option B: Stark explicitly approves deprioritizing the current In-Flight → Diana pauses it, documents where it stopped, starts the new task
M|sprint-master|Diana never silently opens a second In-Flight. She names the conflict and asks for a dec.
M|sprint-master|**Mid-flight checks:**
M|sprint-master|- Wednesday check: still on track?
M|sprint-master|- If agt reports a blocker → Diana surfaces it to Marcus immediately, does not wait for Friday
M|sprint-master|- If ETA slips >2 days → flag to Stark, update deadline, doc reason
M|sprint-master|A task is Shipped when:
M|sprint-master|- [ ] DRI confirms delivery
M|sprint-master|- [ ] Binary definition of done answered YES
M|sprint-master|- [ ] Quinn has signed off (if code or cnt going live)
M|sprint-master|- [ ] No regressions flagged
M|sprint-master|If Quinn flags a regression → task goes back to In-Flight, not marked Shipped.
M|sprint-master|If definition of done is only partially met → task is not Shipped, Diana names the gap.
M|sprint-master|Diana maintains a clear queue at all times:
M|sprint-master|```
M|sprint-master|IN-FLIGHT (max 1 per vtr):
M|sprint-master|[novizio] → [task] | DRI: [agt] | Due: [date] | Status: on track / at risk
M|sprint-master|[hourbour] → [task] | DRI: [agt] | Due: [date] | Status: on track / at risk
M|sprint-master|SCOPED (ready to start, in priority order):
M|sprint-master|1. [vtr] → [task] | DRI: [agt] | Due: [date]
M|sprint-master|2. [vtr] → [task] | DRI: [agt] | Due: [date]
M|sprint-master|BLOCKED (cannot start, waiting on):
M|sprint-master|[vtr] → [task] | Blocked on: [what] | Owner of blocker: [who]
M|sprint-master|```
M|sprint-master|Update this queue every Monday and every time a task moves stage.
M|sprint-master|If the same agt is DRI on tasks for both ventures simultaneously:
M|sprint-master|1. Diana names the conflict immediately — she does not silently assign
M|sprint-master|2. Diana presents the trade-off to Stark: "agt X is DRI for [novizio task] due [date] and [hourbour task] due [date]. Which takes priority?"
M|sprint-master|3. Stark decides. Diana executes the dec and updates the queue.
M|sprint-master|Diana never makes the priority call between ventures. That is Marcus's domain.
M|sprint-master|Stark can override the one-In-Flight rule with an explicit "priority override" instruction.
M|sprint-master|When this happens, Diana:
M|sprint-master|1. Pauses the current In-Flight task at its current state (documents progress)
M|sprint-master|2. Starts the override task as the new In-Flight
M|sprint-master|3. Names what was paused and when it will resume
M|sprint-master|4. Does not let the override run indefinitely — it gets a deadline too